iage. — Many American bearers of this surname are descendants of John Beaumont (1612–47), who came to North America from England in 1630. William Beaumont came from England to Cambridge MA in 1635 and subsequently moved to CT."],"variants":[{"name":"Bement","meanings":["English (Cambridgeshire): variant of   Beaumont  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Beeman","meanings":["English (Kent): occupational name for a beekeeper, from Middle English <i>bee-man</i> ‘bee-keeper’ (Old English <i>bēo</i> + <i>mann</i>).","English (Kent): variant of   Beaumont  .","Americanized form of German   Biemann   or of its Dutch cognate <b>Bieman</b>."]},{"name":"Belmont","meanings":["French and English (of Norman origin): variant of   Beaumont  .","Catalan: habitational name from the placename Bellmont ‘beautiful mountain’. Compare Spanish   Belmonte  ."]},{"name":"Baumunk","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Siegmund.","German: probably a Germanized form of a French Huguenot name <b>Beaumont</b> (see also   Beaumont  )."]},{"name":"Bayman","meanings":["English (mainly Lancashire): variant of   Beaumont  .","Americanized form of German <b>Beumann</b> or <b>Bäumann</b>, variants of   Baumann  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Burgonde de Brienne de Beaumont was born about 1140, in France. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Payen de Rochefort."},"et":{"about 1140–":"umbes 1140–Surnud","1140–1190":"1140–1190","1155–1222":"1155–1222","1165–1222":"1165–1222","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1190":"1190","about 1140":"umbes 1140","1222":"1222","1155":"1155","1165":"1165","1 JAN 1165":"1. jaanuar 1165","1140":"1140","Bressuire,79049,Deux-Sèvres,Nouvelle-Aquitaine,FRANCE,":"Bressuire, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1140–":"noin 1140–Kuollut","1140–1190":"1140–1190","1155–1222":"1155–1222","1165–1222":"1165–1222","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1190":"1190","about 1140":"noin 1140","1222":"1222","1155":"1155","1165":"116